FBIS3-55442 "drsov006_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 Tajikistan Conflicts Continue Along Afghan Border Opposition Party Claims Success LD0701174194 (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan in Tajik 0600 GMT 7 Jan 94 LD0701174194 (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan Language: Tajik Article Type:BFN [Text] Yesterday, heavy clashes took place in one of the posts in Shurobad Rayon, Kulyab Oblast. Military sources in the Islamic Rebirth Party of Tajikistan [words indistinct] report that as a result of these clashes, which continued for (?three hours), 17 government soldiers were killed and even more were wounded. (?One) armored vehicle and one GAZ-66 vehicle were destroyed. One person from among the mujahidin was also wounded. The military sources of the Islamic Rebirth of Tajikistan have denied a report by the press office of the Border Forces of Russia to the effect that an armed group of the opposition was forced to turn back from the border. A (?statement) published by the military committee of the Islamic Rebirth Party of Tajikistan says that the mujahidin of the Islamic Rebirth Party of Tajikistan are functioning not along the borders but inside the territory of Tajikistan. [Words indistinct) the border guards have for some time now lost (?control) of the borders and movement across the borders was even easier than to enter the city of Tursunzoda.
